IBADAN – General Lucky Irabo, Chief of Defence Staff (CDS), has called for a more robust and continuous synergy among the Armed Forces to flush out terrorists within the nooks and crannies of the country. General Irabo who was on a day working visit to 2 Divi­sion, Nigerian Army, Odogbo Fajuyi Cantonment Ibadan, on Thursday along with other service chiefs maintained that his visit became necessary to enforce President Muhamma­du Buhari’s order on flushing our terrorists from their hide­outs in the country. The CDS in his address maintained that it was very important for all the Armed Forces to continue to work in partnership to ensure that the directives recently given by Mr. President to flush out of their various hideouts across the country within few weeks come to fruition. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! “President Buhari has charged us to rebuild and re­store peace in the country and we must do that without any compromise,” he said. “Our purpose of coming here is to demonstrate lead­ership by example, the order given to us should not be seen as a threat, but as an enforce­ment order which requires our collective support and partnership,” he added. Ekiti CP Vows To Halt Herders Trespass On Farmlands Police Declare Ministry Official Wanted Over Child Theft, Trafficking General Irabor also paid a courtesy visit to the State Gov­ernor at the Agodi State Secre­tariat, where he was received with other Service Chiefs by the State Deputy Governor, Engr. Rauf Aderemi Olaniyan, on behalf of the State Gover­nor, Engr. Seyi Makinde.